==Career== In 2014, Jumayyil made his film debut with Ahmed Nimal's ''Aniyaa'', alongside Niuma Mohamed, [[Ismail Rasheed]] and Fathmath Fareela.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://addulive.com/05113572013 |title=Jumayyyil is being launched to the industry with "Aniyaa" |language=Dhivehi |publisher=Addu Live |author=Faisal, Ibrahim |date=4 May 2013 |accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref><ref name="first release">{{cite news|url=http://vnews.mv/18164 |title=First release of the year "Aniyaa" |language=Dhivehi |publisher=Vnews |author=Ali, Safoora |date=29 March 2014 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160609172231/http://vnews.mv/18164 |archivedate=9 June 2016 |accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> Due to some struggle caused during the screening of the film, it failed to garner enough hype to the film. Despite doing average business, Jumayyil's character was met with mixed to positive response from critics.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vaguthu.mv/evaguthu/maldives-film-industry/276537/ |title="Aniyaa" and "Ran Dhari" released |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Vaguthu'' |author=Naail, Ismail |date=25 May 2015 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160609171910/http://www.vaguthu.mv/evaguthu/maldives-film-industry/276537/ |archivedate=9 June 2016 |accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/2873 |title="Aniyaa" and "Ran Dhari" released |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Avas'' |author=Nadheem, Ahmed |date=9 June 2015 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160609172519/https://avas.mv/2873 |archivedate=9 June 2016 |accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> The following year, Jumayyil appeared in Ali Shifau-directed romantic film ''[[Emme Fahu Vindha Jehendhen]]'' opposite Mariyam Majudha, where he portrayed the role of Ryan. The film along with Jumayyil's acting was critically acclaimed. In a pre-premiere review from ''Vaguthu'', Ismail Nail praised Jumayyil and Majudha's chemistry in the film and mentioned how he has improved compared to his work in ''Aniyaa''. The film was the highest grossing film of the year, and was a commercial success.
Jumayyil was next featured in Ali Shifau-directed romantic comedy ''[[Vaashey Mashaa Ekee]]'' (2016) opposite Majudha. In the film, he played the role of Ziyad, a person with a very different taste of his partner.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.avas.mv/12504 |title=A new Film, A new Lover, A new Jumayyil |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Avas'' |author=Nadheem, Ahmed |date=8 January 2016 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160609164655/https://www.avas.mv/12504 |archivedate=9 June 2016 |accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> His performance was positively mentioned in the reviews, Ahmed Nadheem from ''Avas'' picked Jumayyil as the only actor who has shown a major improvement in acting compared to his previous works. He further rated Jumayyil at the same level of Majudha—whom Nadheem considered as the best actor of the film.<ref name="unlimited praise">{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/15516 |title=Vaashey Mashaa Ekee: Unlimited praise |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Avas'' |author=Nasheem, Ahmed |date=6 April 2016 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160606080851/https://avas.mv/15516|archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref> The film was eventually declared as the highest grossing film of the year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/876 |title=Upcoming releases of the year|language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Mihaaru'' |author=Adhushan, Ahmed |date=3 June 2016 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160606085206/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/876 |archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref>
