==Early life== Mohamed Jumayyil's father Ahmed Nimal is one of the established actor and director of the industry.<ref name=football/> Jumayyil went to [[Ahmadhiyya International School|Ahmadiyya Pre-school]] as his first institution. He completed his primary education at Jamaluddin School before completing his secondary education at [[Dharumavantha School]].<ref name=football>{{cite news|url=http://www.vaguthu.mv/evaguthu/arts/291732/ |title=Former Football Player, Now a talented actor |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Vaguthu'' |author=Maahaa, Aishath |date=26 June 2015 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160610085522/http://www.vaguthu.mv/evaguthu/arts/291732/ |archivedate=10 June 2016 |accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref> After completing his [[GCE Ordinary Level]] exams, his father Nimal, inclined Jumayyil to persuade a career in film industry.<ref name=football/> He then offered a chance to act in one of his directed films due to his interest in the industry. During the time, he was a football player at [[B.G. Sports Club]].<ref name=football/> He also worked at [[Singapore Airlines Cargo]], before shifting his job and working as an [[Airport check-in]] staff.<ref name=football/>
